      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "No, you should not take an extra dose of diphenhydramine, as adding more sleep-inducing medications increases the risk of severe drowsiness, accidental falls, or slowed breathing. Allergy medications like diphenhydramine also cause daytime drowsiness, which can dangerously worsen your exhaustion and impair your ability to function. It is important to stick strictly to the medication your doctor prescribed and discuss any lingering sleep concerns with them before trying new remedies.",
